1
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,950
Seems like there's nothing wrong.

2
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:45,870
Yep!

3
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:49,200
I'm kind of hungry again!

4
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:53,380
Don't worry. We'll see an island soon.

5
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:57,000
Let me give you
some extra information while I can.

6
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:03,510
There are a total of 34 islands
surrounding Whole Cake Island.

7
00:02:03,510 --> 00:02:04,930
That many?!

8
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:10,390
There are 34 ministers, one for each island,
to run the place.

9
00:02:10,390 --> 00:02:14,410
They call this vast marine area...

10
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:19,100
Totto Land!

11
00:02:31,330 --> 00:02:36,590
Mm-hm, mm-hm, mm-hm, I see. I'm sorry.

12
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,720
I thought it was an enemy ship.

13
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:46,600
Yeah, I hijacked the ship from a pirate group.
I'll present it to Mama myself.

14
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:51,020
Oh! Do you have 
something sweet in that ship?

15
00:02:51,020 --> 00:02:55,360
– Of course.
– Mama will be happy, then!

16
00:02:55,360 --> 00:03:01,200
It's a surprise.
Don't report to her about that ship.

17
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:04,280
Oh, that's wonderful!

18
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:09,610
Understood! 
Boss Pekoms, that's very cool!

19
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,410
Look at that!

20
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:23,840
Bricks and houses and everything!
They're all...

21
00:03:30,380 --> 00:03:32,720
made of chocolate!

22
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,940
A chocolate town!

23
00:03:34,940 --> 00:03:37,080
It's like a dream!

24
00:03:58,210 --> 00:04:01,800
Wow! There are so many kinds
of people and animals!

25
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:06,970
What the...?! What the...?!
What's with this town?!

26
00:04:06,970 --> 00:04:09,890
Look! Chocolate is pouring out!

27
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:14,950
Oh, I knew you wanted to start
with the fountain of chocolate!

28
00:04:14,950 --> 00:04:16,560
The chocolate spout!

29
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:20,530
"Chocolate Bathhouse"

30
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:20,530
"Chocolate Bathhouse"?!

31
00:04:20,530 --> 00:04:22,110
A chocolate bath?!

32
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,370
– Chocolate clothes?!
– Can you eat them?!

33
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:33,760
I managed to cover for us,
but we should not stay long.

34
00:04:34,370 --> 00:04:38,960
We gotta do what we have to do and just go...

35
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:40,340
Are you done?

36
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:50,680
Wow! This is cute!

37
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,850
Oh, Nami, you look great!

38
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:54,230
Thanks!

39
00:04:55,900 --> 00:05:00,530
Hey, look! My costume looks
quite nice too, right?

40
00:05:01,820 --> 00:05:03,730
Yeah, that's really gorgeous!

41
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:10,990
How's this?
Do I look like a pirate, Broo...

42
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,210
What?

43
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:20,920
Do you want more?

44
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:28,220
It will take one more day to
get to Whole Cake Island, where Sanji is.

45
00:05:28,220 --> 00:05:30,300
Go food shopping.

46
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,780
Okay! Yay!

47
00:05:32,780 --> 00:05:35,310
Pedro, do you have binoculars?!

48
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:39,330
Thanks! Let's see...

49
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:44,310
Wow! It's so diverse here, Pekoms!

50
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:48,660
I see minks, too!
It's like a wonderland!

51
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:52,990
Yes, that's exactly what
Mama's dream is.

52
00:05:52,990 --> 00:06:00,320
Humans, minks, fishmen,
longarms, longlegs, gnomes...

53
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:05,270
A country where all races in the world
can live together without discrimination.

54
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:08,130
No, I mean everything in the world!

55
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,760
Everything in the world?

56
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:16,280
Yes, that's Mama's ideal world, Totto Land!

57
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:21,520
Realize you're already deep
into a great territory!

58
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:25,800
This is Cacao Island, and it's
ruled by the minister of chocolate.

59
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:28,450
This place is called Chocolat Town!

60
00:06:28,450 --> 00:06:31,900
Chocolat Town?! What a wonderful name!

61
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:34,400
Everything in this town is made of chocolate.

62
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:38,080
What?! I love chocolate!
Am I allowed to eat it?!

63
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:42,900
In this town,
you can eat chocolate all you like!

64
00:06:42,900 --> 00:06:43,950
Yes!

65
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:45,710
But be careful!

66
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:48,400
It's against the law to eat
the roof-tile chocolates.

67
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,880
Because they won't be able
to keep off rain or snow.

68
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,830
Window glass is the minister
of candy's jurisdiction,

69
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:55,560
and construction posts are
the minister of biscuit's.

70
00:06:55,560 --> 00:07:00,490
And everything else other than chocolate is
private or public property.

71
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:03,100
Looks delicious...

72
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:05,170
Hey! Were you listening?!

73
00:07:05,170 --> 00:07:07,070
I couldn't understand at all.

74
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:11,530
Say, are their panties
also made of chocolate?

75
00:07:11,530 --> 00:07:13,030
Of course, they are.

76
00:07:14,490 --> 00:07:17,290
I can't wait to see chocolate panties!

77
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,460
We're not here to take a break.

78
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:24,840
Come back as soon as you
finish food shopping.

79
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:29,700
I'll stay on the ship, since they know my face,
but I love chocolate.

80
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,100
Get me some!

81
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:31,930
Okay!

82
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:35,000
Hey, Straw Hat!

83
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:38,070
If you're gonna go,
stop wasting your time and put on your disguise...

84
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:40,700
Luffy and Chopper have
already gone to the town.

85
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:41,390
What?!

86
00:07:41,390 --> 00:07:44,700
Hey, what do you think will
happen if they find out

87
00:07:44,700 --> 00:07:46,400
I brought you guys here?!

88
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,840
Act cautiously!

89
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:51,610
Don't worry!
We'll know where they are soon.

90
00:07:54,410 --> 00:07:56,400
Somebody ate a cafe!

91
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:57,300
There they are!

92
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:58,740
Screw you!

93
00:08:09,710 --> 00:08:13,320
If it were just the chocolate
walls they could be put back later,

94
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,800
but the whole cafe is gone!

95
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:29,690
You guys ate candies,
marshmallows, almonds and jelly beans!

96
00:08:29,690 --> 00:08:33,900
That's a crime of snackalism!
I need to question you!

97
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:35,880
Come to the station with me!

98
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:40,790
But, old man,
there is a good reason for this.

99
00:08:40,790 --> 00:08:43,040
Yeah? Out with it!

100
00:08:43,070 --> 00:08:44,740
It was too delicious!

101
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:47,420
Okay, well said, idiots!
Come with me!

102
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,900
Oh, no! They're gonna get arrested!

103
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:55,090
Don't make a scene, Pedro-san !

104
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:58,050
Wait, Chocopolice-san !

105
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:06,800
♪ Carpet! Carpet! ♪

106
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,610
The carpet is flying...

107
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:11,900
♪ Carpet! Carpet! ♪

108
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:16,410
Oh, you're... the owner!

109
00:09:16,410 --> 00:09:20,450
Oh, more trouble!
The owner of the cafe came!

110
00:09:22,370 --> 00:09:24,710
Look what they've done to your cafe!

111
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:28,290
I can't believe this!

112
00:09:44,930 --> 00:09:50,520
How could you leave this much?
This isn't what we agreed to! Gee!

113
00:09:51,730 --> 00:09:54,780
You have to finish it properly!

114
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,410
Hey, do you know her?

115
00:10:03,410 --> 00:10:05,880
No, I don't. Who is it?

116
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:08,290
And what's that thing on her shoulder?

117
00:10:08,290 --> 00:10:13,500
I thought the combination of jam and biscuits
and chocolate here was delicious!

118
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,170
Here! Try this!

119
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:25,310
How is it?

120
00:10:25,310 --> 00:10:27,640
It's good!

121
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:31,330
Chocopolice-san, I'm sorry.

122
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:34,160
The cafe will be expired soon,

123
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:36,980
so I asked them to eat the whole building!

124
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:41,570
Oh, pardon me! I didn't know
they were a demolition crew!

125
00:10:41,570 --> 00:10:43,350
Come on, guys!

126
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:46,330
You should've had a sign out
when you were working.

127
00:10:46,330 --> 00:10:48,540
There were still some customers too.

128
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:50,880
Well then, if you'll excuse me.

129
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:55,960
Yes, thank you!
And I'm sorry to disturb you, everyone!

130
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:58,330
So it was nothing serious.

131
00:10:58,330 --> 00:10:59,970
Oh, we were so worried.

132
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,180
Oh, yeah!

133
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:07,100
Congratulations on getting married,
Madam Pudding!

134
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:09,540
Your wedding day is approaching
and you're checking in on your cafe?

135
00:11:09,540 --> 00:11:11,140
Don't work too much.

136
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:14,890
We all wish for your happiness!

137
00:11:14,890 --> 00:11:16,780
Thank you!

138
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:20,330
She saved Luffy and Chopper.

139
00:11:20,330 --> 00:11:23,500
She's so kind. I wonder who she is.

140
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,120
They're so lucky!

141
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:29,560
This is how fortune favors
the future pirate king.

142
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,870
Oh?

143
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:32,960
Captain Pedro?!

144
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:39,000
You're Captain Pedro, aren't you?!
I thought so! It's been a while!

145
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,220
Why are you here?

146
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:43,600
I'm just sightseeing. Don't tell anyone I was here.

147
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:47,140
O-Okay. It was a pleasure to see you.

148
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:50,850
You know people in this town, Pedro?

149
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:53,480
I'll tell you later.

150
00:11:56,190 --> 00:12:00,070
So your name is Pudding.
Thank you for helping us!

151
00:12:00,070 --> 00:12:04,080
No, no! I'm the one who
should be thanking you!

152
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,460
Why?

153
00:12:05,460 --> 00:12:07,580
Because you said...

154
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:11,540
"It was too delicious!"

155
00:12:12,030 --> 00:12:17,050
That chocolate at the cafe is a
new blend that I came up with!

156
00:12:17,050 --> 00:12:18,840
Did you like how it melted in your mouth?

157
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:22,200
I added milk to cocoa butter
and highly pure beet sugar

158
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:26,040
and kneaded it for three days
straight at 29 degrees Celsius!

159
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:29,460
I don't know what you're talking about,
but it was so good!

160
00:12:29,460 --> 00:12:31,560
It was!

161
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:35,900
You said it was delicious,
and it really makes me want to cry!

162
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:39,150
Thank you! I'm so happy to hear it!

163
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:40,880
W-W...

164
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:45,490
What a nice girl!

165
00:12:45,490 --> 00:12:47,720
Do you like making chocolate?

166
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:50,120
I love sweets!

167
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:53,660
This town smells like chocolate,
and it's like heaven!

168
00:12:53,660 --> 00:12:55,460
Even the table is chocolate!

169
00:12:55,460 --> 00:12:56,790
It's nice to know that!

170
00:12:56,790 --> 00:13:00,590
We really want to stay
and thank you, Pudding,

171
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:02,490
but we need to go.

172
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:04,970
Yeah? That's too bad.

173
00:13:04,970 --> 00:13:08,180
Before you go, would you like a cup of tea?

174
00:13:08,180 --> 00:13:10,460
I guess you have a sweet taste in your mouth.

175
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:12,560
Tea sounds good!

176
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,770
Okay. I'll be right back.

177
00:13:14,770 --> 00:13:18,980
Oh, what a nice girl!
She's really a nice girl!

178
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:24,450
I haven't asked your name, have I?

179
00:13:24,450 --> 00:13:26,030
I'm Luffy.

180
00:13:26,030 --> 00:13:27,650
The future pirate k–

181
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:28,240
Hey!

182
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,080
What?

183
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:37,080
Luffy?

184
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:13,790
♪ How long do we have until the tea party? ♪

185
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:16,330
♪ Three days, Mama! ♪

186
00:14:16,330 --> 00:14:17,920
♪ Flower! Flower! ♪

187
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,520
♪ I see... ♪

188
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:22,880
♪ What about Germa's son? ♪

189
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:25,340
♪ He's here, Mama! ♪

190
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:28,880
♪ Furniture! Furniture! Furniture! Furniture! ♪

191
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:33,390
♪ There will be a wedding! ♪

192
00:14:33,390 --> 00:14:37,640
♪ How is the cake? ♪

193
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:41,400
♪ The wedding cake! ♪

194
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,150
♪ – The design?
– Okay! ♪

195
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:44,930
♪ – The budget?
– Don't be stingy! ♪

196
00:14:44,930 --> 00:14:46,740
♪ Carefully select the ingredients! ♪

197
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:54,730
♪ Kill the people and rob them! ♪

198
00:14:57,750 --> 00:14:58,790
♪ Eggs! ♪

199
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:02,460
♪ I got them. ♪

200
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:04,670
♪ Flour! ♪

201
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,550
♪ I got it! ♪

202
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:09,930
♪ Fruit! ♪

203
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:13,220
♪ I got it. ♪

204
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:16,140
♪ We'll make it taste good! ♪

205
00:15:16,140 --> 00:15:19,640
♪ Let's eat a delicious cake! ♪

206
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:22,770
♪ Sweet dealings! ♪

207
00:15:23,260 --> 00:15:27,900
♪ The tea party from hell! ♪

208
00:15:29,150 --> 00:15:32,280
♪ – Is this strawberry jam?
– Or somebody's blood? ♪

209
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:35,990
♪ I don't care either way! ♪

210
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:39,960
♪ If you're invited, be there at any cost! ♪

211
00:15:37,940 --> 00:15:39,960
♪ A sweet moment! ♪

212
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:42,460
♪ Sacrifices to the devil! ♪

213
00:15:43,670 --> 00:15:47,210
♪ This is a dream land for everyone... ♪

214
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:52,000
♪ All kinds of races come together... ♪

215
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,750
♪ Totto Land! ♪

216
00:16:06,060 --> 00:16:10,360
♪ Mmm, I can't wait!
I heard he is here. ♪

217
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:14,320
♪ Yes... he is here. ♪

218
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:20,700
♪ Straw Hat! ♪

219
00:16:27,090 --> 00:16:29,090
Luffy is...

220
00:16:32,170 --> 00:16:33,430
Oh, no!

221
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:41,640
Now that I look closer, you look familiar!
Straw Hat Luffy!

222
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:46,520
That's right! I'm gonna be
king of the pirates!

223
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,480
We're totally screwed.

224
00:16:52,190 --> 00:16:56,470
Are you people really
those pirates, the Straw Hats?!

225
00:16:56,470 --> 00:16:57,910
Yes, we are!

226
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:02,120
Sanji-san's comrades?! You're kidding!

227
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:06,110
I'm not kidding! Sanji is our buddy!

228
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:08,840
What? Do you know Sanji?

229
00:17:15,130 --> 00:17:17,340
What?!

230
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:27,440
Are you the daughter of Big Mom
who's gonna get married to Sanji, Pudding?!

231
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:30,650
Mm-hm.

232
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:32,280
Sanji's fiancée...

233
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:36,360
I'm jealous! She'll be such a beautiful wife!

234
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:40,370
W-Wife?!

235
00:17:41,830 --> 00:17:43,870
Oh! But why?!

236
00:17:43,870 --> 00:17:49,580
You people aren't even Mama's allies!
How did you pass the tarte security?

237
00:17:49,580 --> 00:17:53,960
Why did you come?!
Y-You're gonna be killed!

238
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:59,300
You're already in Mama's territory,
and she's a very scary pirate!

239
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:05,330
But I know you people are scary pirates, too!

240
00:18:06,090 --> 00:18:08,150
No!

241
00:18:08,150 --> 00:18:11,730
Wait! Calm down!
We won't get rough with you!

242
00:18:15,140 --> 00:18:17,560
Luffy, what should we do with her?

243
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,860
Don't get rough, Pedro!

244
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:25,750
So you came for Sanji-san...

245
00:18:26,950 --> 00:18:29,750
To take him back.

246
00:18:31,620 --> 00:18:36,920
I knew he didn't consent,
since Mama is so self centered.

247
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:42,940
She even uses her children's weddings
to strengthen her pirate crew.

248
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:48,020
We've given up on marrying someone
freely out of love.

249
00:18:48,020 --> 00:18:51,730
We only have two choices: give up or run.

250
00:18:52,810 --> 00:18:59,240
One of my beloved older sisters... ran off to sea 
to find love. To seek a match of her own.

251
00:18:59,860 --> 00:19:01,780
To seek a match.

252
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:07,880
Just out of curiosity,

253
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:12,000
we have heard that you're the 35th daughter
of the Charlotte family.

254
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,300
Does Big Mom have 35 daughters?

255
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:20,600
Yes, she has 39 daughters and 46 sons.

256
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:23,510
We're 85 brothers and sisters.

257
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:24,470
Oh, my!

258
00:19:24,470 --> 00:19:28,680
Wow! That's so many brothers and sisters!

259
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:35,650
We have different fathers.
Mama had 43 husbands, so we're a family of 129.

260
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:38,690
What... 129?!

261
00:19:38,690 --> 00:19:42,360
Some of my older brothers and sisters
already have children,

262
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:45,910
so if you count them in, there are more.

263
00:19:45,910 --> 00:19:51,210
The Big Mom Pirates consist
mainly of her blood relatives.

264
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:56,920
She's true to her name: Big Mom!

265
00:20:01,210 --> 00:20:05,220
Have you met Sanji?

266
00:20:05,220 --> 00:20:09,270
Y-Y-Yes... just once.

267
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:15,790
Although his eyebrows are twirly,
he is very kind and gentlemanly!

268
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:17,800
♪ Flower! Flower! ♪

269
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,360
Even though he's got heart eyes,

270
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:23,300
he knows so much about making
sweets and taught me a lot!

271
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:25,660
♪ Flower! Flower! ♪

272
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:28,240
We like the same stuff, and he's so manly!

273
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:32,210
I heard his legs are black,
but he's tough and dependable!

274
00:20:32,210 --> 00:20:34,000
He is, isn't he?!

275
00:20:36,580 --> 00:20:39,500
That's not what "Black Leg" means.

276
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:44,510
You really got him! He's a great guy!

277
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:50,470
D-Don't tell me you're in love with...

278
00:20:51,890 --> 00:20:54,770
Are you in love with Sanji-kun ?!

279
00:20:54,770 --> 00:21:00,340
L-L-Love?! Well, I mean...

280
00:21:00,340 --> 00:21:03,360
Mama's decision can't be overturned.

281
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:08,070
And if I marry someone, I prefer, um...

282
00:21:09,330 --> 00:21:13,710
I like Sanji very much, too!
We're the same!

283
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:16,170
No, I can't say such a thing!

284
00:21:17,380 --> 00:21:19,180
Shock!

285
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:25,340
This is totally unexpected!
I can't believe such a lovely girl is the bride!

286
00:21:25,340 --> 00:21:28,510
No wonder Sanji-san's got heart eyes!

287
00:21:30,430 --> 00:21:33,680
We should tie her up!

288
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:44,440
She'll tell them that we're here.

289
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:47,280
If they find us while we're on
one of the outermost islands,

290
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:50,370
we'll never be able to get to Sanji!

291
00:21:50,990 --> 00:21:53,370
How could you say that, Pedro?

292
00:21:53,370 --> 00:21:56,140
How else can we silence her?

293
00:21:56,140 --> 00:22:00,130
Don't forget that she's Big Mom's daughter.

294
00:22:00,130 --> 00:22:05,030
Yeah, but she's scared of her mother too!

295
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:06,800
That's why she'll tell her!

296
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,470
How would you know?!

297
00:22:08,470 --> 00:22:10,720
You stay out of this!

298
00:22:14,640 --> 00:22:15,560
Excuse me.

299
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:27,280
I think I can still let go of my feelings...

300
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:29,910
toward Sanji-san!

301
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:41,080
People in Totto Land...

302
00:22:45,050 --> 00:22:48,340
give their blessings to my marriage.

303
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:53,180
So do the members of the Vinsmoke family.

304
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:56,100
Mama looks forward to the wedding cake.

305
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:03,820
None of us can disobey Mama's order,
so I knew I couldn't marry for love,

306
00:23:03,820 --> 00:23:07,440
but I've been dreaming
ever since I was a child.

307
00:23:08,860 --> 00:23:12,660
Wondering what my husband would be like.

308
00:23:13,830 --> 00:23:17,330
And then, Sanji-san came along.

309
00:23:35,500 --> 00:23:39,310
I was surprised,
because he was such a wonderful man.

310
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:44,650
But, he actually said to me in the end,

311
00:23:47,570 --> 00:23:51,360
"I want to marry you, but I can't do it."

312
00:23:54,480 --> 00:23:57,740
"I want to go back to my friends."

313
00:23:57,740 --> 00:24:02,170
What?! Sanji rejected a girl?!

314
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:09,630
But... it's good to know...
I knew he wanted to continue the adventure!

315
00:24:11,170 --> 00:24:14,550
It wasn't just him who wanted to be back,

316
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:20,930
because you all actually came here
to take him back at the risk of your lives.

317
00:24:22,130 --> 00:24:24,600
Even if this is Mama's decision,

318
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:29,150
it'd be hard for me to stay with someone
who didn't want to get married.

319
00:24:29,820 --> 00:24:35,910
And most of all, I know you all
care about Sanji-san very much,

320
00:24:36,810 --> 00:24:39,200
and I can't take him away from you.

321
00:24:40,910 --> 00:24:45,130
He said he wanted to go
back to his friends too.

322
00:24:45,130 --> 00:24:49,050
Then all I can do for him
is help him with that.

323
00:24:50,210 --> 00:24:52,010
Take this route.

324
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:55,560
This is the only way you can get there

325
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:58,720
without Mama finding out. 
Only we siblings know about it!

326
00:24:59,370 --> 00:25:00,930
Is that where Sanji is?

327
00:25:01,510 --> 00:25:06,860
If you go along this route,
you can get to Whole Cake Island.

328
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:10,730
But Mama won't let go of Sanji-san.

329
00:25:11,230 --> 00:25:15,700
So let's meet up at the southwest coast of
 Whole Cake Island tomorrow.

330
00:25:17,530 --> 00:25:21,080
I'll promise to bring Sanji-san there.

331
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:23,290
I'll cooperate with you!

332
00:25:23,290 --> 00:25:26,900
Is it okay?
Won't you get punished by Big Mom?

333
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:30,420
I'm her biological daughter.
Don't worry.

334
00:25:30,420 --> 00:25:34,380
You're in enemy territory.
Worry about yourself.

335
00:25:34,380 --> 00:25:35,760
Pudding...

336
00:25:41,890 --> 00:25:44,850
But is it really okay?

337
00:25:44,850 --> 00:25:48,400
Sanji-san and you all care about each other.

338
00:25:50,610 --> 00:25:54,150
Pudding-san, you're so...

339
00:25:54,150 --> 00:25:58,860
It's a bit of a shame,
but my next husband to-be...

340
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:02,040
could be someone even nicer!

341
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:08,460
H-How wonderful this girl is!
Is she really the emperor's daughter?!

342
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,670
Thank you, Pudding!

343
00:26:13,670 --> 00:26:15,510
You're welcome!

344
00:26:20,080 --> 00:26:23,520
Madam Pudding, we're here to pick you up.

345
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:25,430
One moment!

346
00:26:25,430 --> 00:26:29,060
I'm working now, so wait a second.

347
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:35,060
You need to stop working until the wedding,
Madam Pudding.

348
00:26:35,060 --> 00:26:37,950
But I have customers...

349
00:26:37,950 --> 00:26:39,910
You have to prepare for the wedding, too.

350
00:26:47,830 --> 00:26:52,250
Oh, it's you! The groceries
that you ordered are ready.

351
00:26:52,250 --> 00:26:54,090
They're there, so just take them.

352
00:26:54,090 --> 00:26:55,800
Oh, there they are!

353
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:57,080
Can you carry them?

354
00:26:57,080 --> 00:26:59,180
Thanks. We'll be fine!

355
00:27:02,090 --> 00:27:03,620
Choco-burger?!

356
00:27:03,620 --> 00:27:07,640
Don't look at other stuff!
Let's go! Pekoms is waiting for us!

357
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:10,690
I want the choco-burger, Nami!

358
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:15,360
– Choco-pasta.
– Choco-fried chicken.

359
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:18,530
We have enough food! Come on!

360
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:23,200
Oh?

361
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:25,030
Pekoms?

362
00:27:25,030 --> 00:27:26,520
Did you find him?

363
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:27,680
No!

364
00:27:27,680 --> 00:27:29,720
This is strange.

365
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:32,120
Doing number two, maybe?
What about the bathroom?

366
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,250
Hey!

367
00:27:35,590 --> 00:27:37,300
There is a message in the bathroom!

368
00:27:45,330 --> 00:27:47,310
"Turn back"?

369
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:51,240
– Did Pekoms write this?
– Who else would do that?

370
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:52,860
Did somebody invade?

371
00:27:52,860 --> 00:27:56,090
Has Pekoms been abducted?

372
00:27:56,090 --> 00:27:59,820
Maybe they've found out about us.

373
00:27:59,820 --> 00:28:02,570
In any event, this is serious.

374
00:28:02,570 --> 00:28:04,990
"Turn back"

375
00:28:05,020 --> 00:28:09,520
"Turn back" means if we don't turn back,
something's gonna happen.

376
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,300
Yeah.

377
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:13,580
Okay, everyone, keep that in mind!

378
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:22,260
Let's keep going!

379
00:28:22,260 --> 00:28:23,510
What?

380
00:28:23,510 --> 00:28:27,180
This is getting exciting!

381
00:29:10,930 --> 00:29:12,480
Damn!

382
00:29:20,570 --> 00:29:22,260
– All done?
– Yes, sir.

383
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:24,200
Okay, let's go.

384
00:29:26,350 --> 00:29:29,080
How dare you kill my wife?

385
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:31,660
How dare you kill my children?

386
00:29:31,660 --> 00:29:35,250
How dare you destroy my country?

387
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:39,840
You're Germa, aren't you?!
You guys are not human!

388
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:41,090
Wall.

389
00:30:01,940 --> 00:30:03,990
I can't believe it took four hours.

390
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:08,610
I have to attend my brother's wedding.

391
00:30:12,370 --> 00:30:15,330
I have no interest in your family.

392
00:30:16,950 --> 00:30:20,290
Nor your war for that matter.

393
00:30:27,030 --> 00:30:28,930
It's finished.

394
00:30:28,930 --> 00:30:33,560
How could a war between such
weak countries last two years?

395
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:36,770
– The commission?
– I got it.

396
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:55,660
– Thank you!
– Thank you!

397
00:30:55,660 --> 00:31:01,640
Our country has been saved.
Did we ask demons for help?

398
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:06,260
No, we didn't! They're angels!

399
00:31:07,070 --> 00:31:12,260
Drop your weapons!
The war is over! It's over!

400
00:31:15,680 --> 00:31:17,640
Thank you, Germa!

401
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:20,980
Germa 66! Hurray!

402
00:31:20,980 --> 00:31:26,280
Germa! Germa! Germa! Germa!

403
00:31:31,530 --> 00:31:34,160
The wedding is in three days.

404
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:37,840
Two days is enough
to get to Whole Cake Island.

405
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:40,160
What about Sanji?

406
00:31:40,160 --> 00:31:42,380
He's already here.

407
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:46,090
Oh, great. I can't wait to see him.

408
00:31:46,090 --> 00:31:48,330
Yeah, right!

409
00:31:48,330 --> 00:31:50,320
See you in two days.

